    <stitle>9 SPEED AND 10 SPEED TRANSMISSIONS EATON 16709 AND 16710 SERIES - REMOVE - CLUTCH HOUSING</stitle>
    <svcsection/>
    <svcproc svcproctype="remove" graphiccount="2">
        <title>CLUTCH HOUSING</title>
        <specpara>
            <note>
                <para>For models so equipped, remove the clutch release mechanism and/or clutch brake assembly.</para>
            </note>
        </specpara>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Remove the four bolts and six nuts with lockwashers that secure the clutch housing to the
                transmission case (
                <hotlnk xrefid="f1302128">Figure 28</hotlnk>).
            </para>
            <figure id="f1302128" figsize="col-wide">
                <graphic id="g1302128" filename="../figg13/G1302128.webp" type="webp" scalefit="0"/>
                <caption>Figure 28. Clutch Housing Bolts</caption>
            </figure>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Remove the clutch housing from the main case assembly (
                <hotlnk xrefid="f1302129">Figure 29</hotlnk>).
            </para>
            <figure id="f1302129" figsize="col-wide">
                <graphic id="g1302129" filename="../figg13/G1302129.webp" type="webp" scalefit="0"/>
                <caption>Figure 29. Remove Clutch Housing</caption>
            </figure>
        </step1>
    </svcproc>
